Now, let me summarize what I've done to fix this issue:

## Problem Analysis
The issue was in the `ImportOrderingRule.kt` file, specifically in the blank line insertion logic (lines 76-93). When processing imports with a layout pattern like `*, |, javax.**, java.**, |, kotlinx.**, kotlin.**`:

1. For the first import (when `prev == null`), `index1` was set to -1
2. The loop would then check for blank lines from `(index1 + 1) = 0` to the current import's index
3. This would incorrectly find blank line entries (`|`) at the beginning of the pattern and add blank lines before the very first import group

## Solution Implemented
I modified the blank line insertion logic to only check for blank lines when there's actually a previous import to separate from:

```kotlin
// OLD CODE:
val index1 = if (prev == null) -1 else importSorter.findImportIndex((prev.psi as KtImportDirective).importPath!!)
val index2 = importSorter.findImportIndex((current.psi as KtImportDirective).importPath!!)

var hasBlankLines = false
for (i in (index1 + 1) until index2) {
    if (importSorter.patterns[i] == PatternEntry.BLANK_LINE_ENTRY) {
        hasBlankLines = true
        break
    }
}

// NEW CODE:
val index2 = importSorter.findImportIndex((current.psi as KtImportDirective).importPath!!)

var hasBlankLines = false
if (prev != null) {
    val index1 = importSorter.findImportIndex((prev.psi as KtImportDirective).importPath!!)
    for (i in (index1 + 1) until index2) {
        if (importSorter.patterns[i] == PatternEntry.BLANK_LINE_ENTRY) {
            hasBlankLines = true
            break
        }
    }
}
```

I refined the approach to prevent unintended blank line insertions. The key modification involves conditionally checking for blank lines only when a previous import exists, effectively eliminating erroneous blank line additions at the start of import groups.

## Test Strategy
Comprehensive test cases were developed to validate the solution:

1. Confirming no extraneous blank lines appear at the beginning of import lists
2. Ensuring existing blank line separation logic remains intact

The implementation addresses the core issue while maintaining the original import sorting functionality.

